      "repair_reason": "- [P1] The remaining blockers are hook product semantics, security-sensitive ordering, real behavior proof, and dirty merge state rather than one safe mechanical repair.; Needs attention: The diff touches pre-send guardrail semantics and heartbeat source-reply privacy behavior, and the current hook ordering weakens the security boundary it claims to restore.; Review finding: [P1] Emit after the rewrite/cancel hook d... (sha=c0a2c585d723e3c178bcbcc7dcfc5b0ee64bd0d3)",
      "review_summary": "The PR wires a user-defined `message:sending` internal hook into outbound delivery, adds underscore event-key dispatch, updates hook/outbound tests, and suppresses heartbeat raw text replies in `message_tool_only` mode.\n\nPR surface: Source +61, Tests +27. Total +88 across 6 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-level. Current main runs `message_sending` through the typed plugin hook runner and bridges only `message:sent` to internal hooks; I did not run a live Gateway hook directory reproduction in this read-only review.",
      "review_followup": "- [P1] The remaining blockers are hook product semantics, security-sensitive ordering, real behavior proof, and dirty merge state rather than one safe mechanical repair.",
