      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(hooks): wire message:sending internal hook to user-defined hooks",
        "body": "## Problem\nInternal `message_sending` hook fires only through the typed plugin hook runner and bridges only `message:sent` to internal hooks. User-defined hook handlers configured under `message:sending` never receive outbound message events.\n\nFixes #73542\n\n## Root Cause\nThe internal hook bridge only registered `message:sent` (post-send notification) and had no internal bridge for `message:sending` (pre-send interception). Underscore-key dispatch (`message_sending` ↔ `message:sending`) was also missing.\n\n## Fix\nAdd an internal `message:sending` bridge with underscore-key dispatch, wire it into core outbound delivery in `src/infra/outbound/deliver.ts`, and update hook/outbound tests. Also add heartbeat `message_tool_only` raw reply suppression.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: User-defined `message:sending` hook handlers never fired because no internal bridge existed from the hook runner to outbound message delivery. After the fix, `message:sending` fires through the internal hook bridge before messages are delivered.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux (Node.js 22), openclaw development checkout with pnpm, vitest 4.1.8.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `node ./node_modules/.bin/vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.infra.config.ts src/hooks/internal-hooks.test.ts src/infra/outbound/deliver.test.ts`\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n```\n$ node ./node_modules/.bin/vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.infra.config.ts src/hooks/internal-hooks.test.ts src/infra/outbound/deliver.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/user/openclaw\n\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  192 passed (192)\n   Duration  ~17s\n```\n- **Observed result after fix**: All 192 hook and outbound delivery tests pass, covering the internal `message:sending` bridge, underscore-key dispatch (`message_sending` ↔ `message:sending`), and heartbeat tool-only suppression. User-defined `message:sending` hooks now receive outbound message events before delivery.\n- **What was not tested**: Full end-to-end delivery with a connected channel (Telegram/WhatsApp) was not manually tested. The tests verify the internal bridge wiring and hook dispatch logic in isolation.",
